                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At his news conference on September 21, Mr. Truman was asked the following
                    question: “Mr. President, have you decided what our troops will do when they
                    reach the 38th parallel in Korea? President Truman responded as follows: “No, I
                    have not. That is a matter for the <pb facs="0768" n="748" xml:id="pg_748"/>
                    United Nations to decide. That is a United Nations force, and we are one of the
                    many who are interested in that situation. It will be worked out by the United
                    Nations and I will abide by the decision that the United Nations makes.” (<hi
                        rend="italic">Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States: Harry S.
                        Truman, 1950</hi>, page 644)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
